This paper deals with data structures and algorithms for compressed trees, which are a fundamental topic in computer science. The focus is on achieving constant-time traversal and subtree equality checking, which are important operations in many applications. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), which covers research on efficient data structures and algorithms. 

The paper also involves concepts from computational complexity (cs.CC), such as time and space complexity analysis, as well as machine learning (cs.LG) and information theory (cs.IT), which are relevant for understanding the compression techniques used. Finally, the paper may also be relevant to the field of deep learning (cs.DL), which often involves processing large trees or graphs.
